<h1>Machine Shop Practice</h1>

<ol type=1><p>

<li>Visit a machine shop, trade school, or a factory using or manufacturing machinery. Observe the benchwork, power equipment, machine tools, and safety devices to protect workers, and make a report of this visit.<p>

<li>Name the uses of the following: lathe, planer, shaper, power and drill press.<p>

<li>Name and tell the uses of at least ten (10) of the principal hand tools used by machinists.<p>

<li>Show the divisions of a foot, an inch, a meter, and a centimeter.<p>

<li>Make a rough sketch of a ball peen hammer head.<p>

<li>Demonstrate how to read a vernier and a micrometer caliper.<p>

<li>Enumerate ten (10) safety rules to be followed while operating machines.<p>

<li>Demonstrate the operation of a machine in a machine shop, observing the proper safety rules.</ol>


</span><p>
